 :Camel Book: n. Universally recognized nickname for the book "Programming
Perl", by Larry Wall and Randal L. Schwartz, O'Reilly and Associates 1991,
ISBN 0-937175-64-1 (second edition 1996, ISBN 1-56592-149-6; third edition
2000, 0-596-00027-8, adding as auhors Tom Christiansen and Jon Orwant but
dropping Randal Schwartz). The definitive reference on {Perl}.